    <h2>Who Is Skruf?</h2>
    <p>Skruf is not a new startup or Instagram-famous brand. It's a <strong>legacy Swedish snus maker founded in 2002 by Skruf Snus AB and now owned by Imperial Brands</strong>, a multinational consumer goods company listed on the FTSE. Imperial Brands operates globally under all applicable tobacco regulations including EU TPD 2014/40/EU. Skruf represents the authenticity of Swedish nicotine tradition — the kind of brand Swedish users grew up with, before the pouch explosion of the 2010s.</p>
    <p>Unlike brands chasing extreme strength or viral aesthetics, Skruf focuses on <strong>balanced craft flavours designed for everyday enjoyment</strong> and <strong>consistent quality across all strength tiers</strong>. If you value heritage over hype, Skruf's track record speaks for itself. Compare Skruf with other heritage brands in our <a href="/blog/best-nicotine-pouches-2026">2026 nicotine pouch rankings</a>.</p>

    <h2>The S2/S3/S4 Strength System Explained</h2>
    <p>Skruf uses a tiered numbering system that makes strength selection straightforward:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>S2 (Light):</strong> 6 mg nicotine — entry-level; ideal for beginners or all-day use without heavy stimulation.</li>
        <li><strong>S3 (Medium):</strong> 9 mg nicotine — moderate; suits regular users comfortable with sustained nicotine hit.</li>
        <li><strong>S4 (Strong):</strong> 11–12 mg nicotine — high; for experienced users seeking intense satisfaction.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>This system means <strong>you can find the same flavour at multiple strengths</strong>. Want Fresh Mint? You can get S2 (6 mg), S3 (9 mg), or S4 (11 mg). This flexibility is Skruf's design genius and sets it apart from single-product brands.</p>

    <h2>Complete Flavour Range</h2>

