    <h2>FAQ</h2>

    <h3>What is Skruf and who makes it?</h3>
    <p>Skruf is a Swedish nicotine pouch brand owned by Imperial Brands, a global consumer goods company. Founded in 2002 by Skruf Snus AB in Sweden, Skruf represents the original craft snus heritage and remains one of Sweden's most respected heritage brands in the nicotine category.</p>

    <h3>What does the S2, S3, S4 strength system mean?</h3>
    <p>Skruf uses a strength numbering system: S2 is light (6 mg), S3 is medium (9 mg), and S4 is strong (11–12 mg). This tiered approach helps users choose the right strength progressively. Unlike single-product brands, Skruf offers multiple flavours at each strength level, giving flexibility across the range.</p>

    <h3>Which Skruf product is the strongest?</h3>
    <p>Skruf's strongest products are Fresh Freeze Ultra (11.5 mg), Crystal Fresh Extra Strong (11.5 mg), and several S4 offerings including Intense Spearmint Ice and Intense Peppermint Ice (both 11.3 mg). Fresh Apple Extra Strong at 11 mg is also a popular ultra-strong choice for fruit flavour lovers.</p>

    <h3>Is Skruf better than Loop or other brands?</h3>
    <p>There is no universally 'better' brand — preference depends on strength, flavour, and pouch format. Skruf excels at heritage flavours (licorice, berry) and craft authenticity. Loop focuses on Nordic minimalism. We recommend trying both to discover your preference. See our <a href="/blog/loop-vs-skruf">comparison guide</a> for detailed differences.</p>

